"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-14-Exclusive-Chinese-equestrian-star-Alex-Hua-Tian-ready-for-Paris-2024-1ve7Q6V2Ip2-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  Eventing rider Alex Hua Tian, who won China's first Asian Games equestrian golds last year in Hangzhou, will compete at the Olympics for the fourth time in Paris, after previously appearing in Beijing, Rio, and Tokyo.  CGTN Sports Scene's Greg Laffradi recently talked to the 34-year-old about his expectations for this year's Olympics, the future of his sport in China, and his thoughts on Euro 2024.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"